 or that you provide to us. Our Privacy Policy shall also apply to your use of our Platform and by using our Platform, you consent to such processing and you warrant that all data provided by you is accurate.<strong></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>14.</strong><strong>Further User Assurance</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-IN\">By using our Platform and/ or any of its Content, you represent and warrant that all information you submit, including without limitation, any registration or subscription details, is truthful, lawful and accurate and that you agree to maintain the accuracy of such information. You further represent and warrant that your use of the Platform and/ or any of its Content shall be solely for your personal use and you shall not authorize others to use your account, including your profile or email address and that you are solely responsible for all content published or displayed through your account, including any email messages, and your interactions with other Users and you shall abide by all applicable local, state, national and foreign laws, treaties and regulations, including those related to data privacy, international communications and the transmission of technical or personal data.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-IN\">All necessary licenses, consents, permissions and rights are owned by you and there is no need for any payment or permission or authorization required from any other party or entity to use the Platform and/ or any of its Content.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\">15.</span></strong><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\">Termination</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-IN\">In accessing and using our Platform, you agree to comply with all applicable laws and further agree not to take any action that would compromise the security or viability of our Platform. We reserve the sole right to terminate any of the User&rsquo;s access to the Platform at any time for any reason. The terms hereunder regarding Accuracy of Information, Limitation of Liability and Indemnity shall survive termination.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\">16.</span></strong><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\">Limitation of Liability</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In no event will we, or our directors, employees, agents, licensors, partners or suppliers be liable to you for any special, indirect, incidental, consequential, punitive, reliance, or exemplary damages (including without limitation lost business opportunities, lost revenues, or loss of anticipated profits or any other pecuniary or non-pecuniary loss or damage of any nature whatsoever) arising out of or relating to (a) these Terms of Use; or (b) your use or inability to use the Platform or any of its Content. In no event will we or any of our contractors, directors, employees, agents, third party partners, licensors or suppliers&rsquo; total liability to you for all damages, liabilities, losses, and causes of action arising out of or relating to (a) these Terms of Use; or (b) your use or inability to use the Platform or any of its Content; or (c) any other interactions with us, however caused and whether arising in contract, tort including negligence, warranty or otherwise, exceed the amount paid by you, if any, for using the portion of the Platform or any of its Content. In no event will we or any of our contractors, directors, employees, agents, third party partners, licensors or suppliers be liable to you for any losses, damage, liabilities, and causes of action arising out of any act, omission or negligence to which you contributed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\">17.</span></strong><strong><span lang=\"EN-IN\">Indemnity</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You agree to indemnify, save and hold us and our affiliates, contractors, employees officers, directors, agents and third party partners harmless from any and all claims, losses, damages, liabilities, costs and expenses, including without limitation, legal fees and expenses arising out of or related to your use or misuse of the Platform or any of its Content, any violation of these Terms of Use, or any of the covenants made by you herein.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>18.</strong><strong>Governing Law and Jurisdiction</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>These Terms of Use are governed by, and construed in accordance with the laws of India. You agree, as we do, to submit to the exclusive jurisdiction of courts in Bangalore, India.<strong></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>19.</strong><strong>Grievance Officer</strong></p>\r\n<p>The name and contact details of our Grievance Officer are as follows:<strong></strong></p>\r\n<p>Ganesh Arunachala</p>\r\n<p>Vice President - Chief Assurance Officer - Corporate Data Protection</p>\r\n<p>2350 Mission College Blvd., Suite 1250, Santa Clara, CA 95054</p>\r\n<p>E-Mail:<span lang=\"EN-IN\"><a href=\"mailto:ganesh.arunachala@trasers.com\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">ganesh.arunachala@trasers.com</span></a></span></p>\r\n<p>The Grievance Officer can be contacted to report abuse, or to complain against any content hosted, transmitted, published, updated or shared on our Platform.</p>\r\n');
